  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, the results suggest that achieving fairness in AI is a dynamic and multifaceted challenge, requiring ongoing attention, innovation, and collaboration among researchers, developers, ethicists, and policymakers.Future research should focus on exploring alternative data sources, training methodologies, and model architectures that can reduce bias while enhancing performance.",
    "The development of more sophisticated benchmarking tools that can accurately reflect the complexities of real-world applications is also crucial.",
    "Additionally, engaging with diverse communities to understand the broader societal impacts of LLMs will be essential in guiding ethical AI development.",
    "Ultimately, this study contributes to the broader discourse on AI ethics and fairness, providing valuable insights and directions for future work in creating more equitable and responsible AI technologies."
